statement: F. Binary Notationtime limit per test2 secondsmemory limit per test256 megabytesinputstdinoutputstdoutYou are given a positive integern. Output its binary notation.InputThe only line of input data contains an integern(1 ≤n≤ 106).OutputOutput the binary notation ofn(without any leading zeros).ExamplesInput5Output101Input101Output1100101NoteIn the first example5 = 1 * 22+ 0 * 21+ 1 * 20.
